          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 46</h1><p><strong>Questions 27 - 30</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>27 To which place does the university ID card NOT allow free entrance?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The university library</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    The university computer centre</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    The university sports centre</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>28 What does the member of staff say about university computers?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Students can book a session to use one by completing a form in the library.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    They are no longer available to students.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    It can be hard to find a free one at certain times during the academic year.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>29 Why do members of the sports facilities need to also have a Student Union membership?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    It allows them to access university sports matches at the indoor sports halls.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    It covers them in case of accident or injury when doing sport.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    It gives free entry to certain classes, such as pilates or circuit training.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>30 Which lecture will the student go to?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Accountancy</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Economics</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Operations management</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
